text.tspan: So let's do this..
You can tap on the bottom bar to move pad
to that position.
However, once the pad moves, you cannot
move it again until a ball touches the pad.
(Tap to continue)
When the ball hits the bricks,
Orbiters are randomly awarded.
Orbiters prevent your ball from being
destroyed if the pad misses it.
Also, one orbiter means you have
action you can choose to execute.
More on actions next...
The yellow spot in the middle can
be pressed (tap and hold) to invoke
the actions menu.
To choose an action,
while holding your finger
on screen move on the
desired action and release.
Note: one action per orbiter
Do be aware that bricks can
ocassionally start shooting.
Also, as you advance through the game,
bricks will try to dodge the ball.
This guy on the left is NOT a friend of the
ball, so try and make the ball avoid it.
You are equiped with one
more ability. You can alter
the course of the ball by
tap-and-holding the right
or left of the screen.
The amount that you can do
this is indicated by the bar
on the top.
(It refills automatically)
Oh! And the game is programmed to
get harder as you progress.
Have fun!
The game is lost when no health is left
or when there are no balls left.
